{"parse":{"title":"Miscegenation hoax","pageid":58492956,"revid":859713214,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>Miscegenation: The Theory of the Blending of the Races, Applied to the American White Man and Negro</b></i> is a December 1863 <a href=\"/wiki/Hoax\" title=\"Hoax\">hoax</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Pamphlet\" title=\"Pamphlet\">pamphlet</a> created by <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_World\" title=\"New York World\">New York World</a></i> staff as part of an anti-Lincoln <a href=\"/wiki/Copperhead_(politics)\" title=\"Copperhead (politics)\">Copperhead</a> campaign leading up to the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_presidential_election,_1864\" title=\"United States presidential election, 1864\">1864 presidential election</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The 72-page piece coined the term <i><a href=\"/wiki/Miscegenation\" title=\"Miscegenation\">miscegenation</a></i> (from the Latin <i>miscere</i> \"to mix\" + <i>genus</i> \"kind\") and was put together by <i>World</i> managing editor <a href=\"/wiki/David_Goodman_Croly\" title=\"David Goodman Croly\">David Goodman Croly</a> and reporter George Wakeman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The work purports to be a sincere advocacy of the virtues of racial mixing, but it is a <a href=\"/wiki/Literary_forgery\" title=\"Literary forgery\">literary forgery</a> intended to argue against racial equality, and to blame the Lincoln administration for allegedly supporting this goal.  The authors unsuccessfully attempted to trick Lincoln into endorsing the work.  The <i>World</i> also featured a hoax about a \"Miscegenation Ball\" with interracial dancing alleged to have been held at a Republican function in New York City during the campaign.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Miscegenation_hoax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Kaplan, Sidney (1949). \"The Miscegenation Issue in the Election of 1864\". <i>The Journal of Negro History</i>. <b>34</b> (3): 274\u2013343. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2307/2715904\">10.2307/2715904</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/2715904\">2715904</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Journal+of+Negro+History&amp;rft.atitle=The+Miscegenation+Issue+in+the+Election+of+1864&amp;rft.volume=34&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=274-343&amp;rft.date=1949&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F2715904&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2715904&amp;rft.aulast=Kaplan&amp;rft.aufirst=Sidney&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMiscegenation+hoax\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Waugh, John (2009-04-30). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=NDzSypIhISUC&amp;pg=PA318\"><i>Reelecting Lincoln: The Battle For The 1864 Presidency</i></a>. Da Capo Press, Incorporated. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780786747115\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780786747115\">9780786747115</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Reelecting+Lincoln%3A+The+Battle+For+The+1864+Presidency&amp;rft.pub=Da+Capo+Press%2C+Incorporated&amp;rft.date=2009-04-30&amp;rft.isbn=9780786747115&amp;rft.aulast=Waugh&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DNDzSypIhISUC%26pg%3DPA318&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMiscegenation+hoax\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Holzer, Harold (2013-05-02). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/05/02/how-a-racist-newspaper-defeated-lincoln-in-new-york-in-the-1864-election\">\"How a Racist Newspaper Defeated Lincoln in New York in the 1864 Election\"</a>. <i>The Daily Beast</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-09-15</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Daily+Beast&amp;rft.atitle=How+a+Racist+Newspaper+Defeated+Lincoln+in+New+York+in+the+1864+Election&amp;rft.date=2013-05-02&amp;rft.aulast=Holzer&amp;rft.aufirst=Harold&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Farticles%2F2013%2F05%2F02%2Fhow-a-racist-newspaper-defeated-lincoln-in-new-york-in-the-1864-election&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMiscegenation+hoax\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-hea